body:
**Originally observed behaviour:**
1) Hono PA connecting to Hono Messaging
2) Due to issues on network layer the IP address of Hono Messaging was a blackhole (receiving messages but never replying)
3) Due to ProtonClientOptions.setReconnectAttempts(-1)
io/vertx/core/impl/netClientImpl.java:doConnect will retry forever (TCP SYN).

**Points that need improvement:**
* This will not perform a new lookup of the IP address. Especially in the situations when a DNS name is backed by many (changing) IP addresses, the client might be able to recover by doing a fresh lookup.
* Hono disconnect handler does not get called, thus no logging.

**I was able to reproduce the behaviour using the Example client:**
* ProtonClientOptions.setReconnectAttempts(-1)
* Use an http endpoint as destination (which will silently discard amqp traffic)
* I see the same TCP SYN forever without recovery

My suggestion is to change the Proton reconnect to a value that makes sense: 2
If the handshake does not work on the Proton level, control shall move back to Hono's reconnect handler.

We can then introduce a HonoReconnectAttempts that will control the number of reattempts done by Hono's reconnect handler.

The reason I am proposing this is that in my opinion a client should behave as graceful as possible. With this behavioural change, the client will be able to recover from some real world error conditions.

Some pseudo code:
```
diff --git a/client/src/main/java/org/eclipse/hono/client/impl/HonoClientImpl.java b/client/src/main/java/org/eclipse/hono/client/impl/HonoClientImpl.java
index 27c8efa..3872ace 100644
--- a/client/src/main/java/org/eclipse/hono/client/impl/HonoClientImpl.java
+++ b/client/src/main/java/org/eclipse/hono/client/impl/HonoClientImpl.java
@@ -30,6 +30,7 @@ import java.util.function.BiConsumer;
 import java.util.function.Consumer;
 import java.util.function.Supplier;
 
+import io.vertx.core.net.NetClientOptions;
 import org.apache.qpid.proton.amqp.Symbol;
 import org.apache.qpid.proton.message.Message;
 import org.eclipse.hono.cache.CacheProvider;
@@ -389,13 +390,16 @@ public class HonoClientImpl implements HonoClient {
             final Handler<AsyncResult<HonoClient>> connectionHandler,
             final Handler<ProtonConnection> disconnectHandler) {
 
+        int honoReconnects = 1000;
+        LOG.info("Failed :(", connectionFailureCause);
+
         if (shuttingDown.get()) {
             // no need to try to re-connect
             connectionHandler.handle(Future.failedFuture(new IllegalStateException("client is shut down")));
-        } else if (clientOptions.getReconnectAttempts() - reconnectAttempts.get() == 0) {
+        } else if (honoReconnects - reconnectAttempts.get() == 0) {
             reconnectAttempts = new AtomicInteger(0);
             LOG.debug("max number of attempts [{}] to re-connect to peer [{}:{}] have been made, giving up",
-                    clientOptions.getReconnectAttempts(), connectionFactory.getHost(), connectionFactory.getPort());
+                    honoReconnects, connectionFactory.getHost(), connectionFactory.getPort());
             if (connectionFailureCause == null) {
                 connectionHandler.handle(Future.failedFuture(
                         new ServerErrorException(HttpURLConnection.HTTP_UNAVAILABLE, "failed to connect")));
diff --git a/example/src/main/java/org/eclipse/hono/example/AbstractExampleClient.java b/example/src/main/java/org/eclipse/hono/example/AbstractExampleClient.java
index 6a9d135..35ff0d9 100644
--- a/example/src/main/java/org/eclipse/hono/example/AbstractExampleClient.java
+++ b/example/src/main/java/org/eclipse/hono/example/AbstractExampleClient.java
@@ -35,6 +35,7 @@ abstract class AbstractExampleClient {
 
     protected final Logger LOG = LoggerFactory.getLogger(getClass());
     protected final int DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT_MILLIS = 1000;
+    protected final int DEFAULT_PROTON_CONNECT_RETRIES = 2;
 
     protected Context ctx;
     @Value(value = "${tenant.id}")
@@ -66,6 +67,6 @@ abstract class AbstractExampleClient {
     }
 
     protected final ProtonClientOptions getClientOptions() {
-        return new ProtonClientOptions().setConnectTimeout(DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT_MILLIS).setReconnectAttempts(2);
+        return new ProtonClientOptions().setConnectTimeout(DEFAULT_CONNECT_TIMEOUT_MILLIS).setReconnectAttempts(DEFAULT_PROTON_CONNECT_RETRIES);
     }
 }
```
